ong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 04:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/04/stardom-is-not-a-worthy-pursuit-julia-louis-dreyfus-on-sexism-ageing-and-fighting-fascism" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/04/breaking-the-waves-review-emily-watson-adds-brilliance-to-von-triers-windup-of-a-movie" target="_blank">Breaking the Waves review – Emily Watson adds brilliance to von Trier’s windup of a movie - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Lars von Trier’s deadpan-tragic fantasy of emotional pain from 1996 is re-released as part of a retrospective dedicated to this director. It is magnificently acted, stylishly composed and entirely ridiculous from beginning to end. Emily Watson brings generous substance to a punishing role as a dangerously selfless wife.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 06:00:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/04/breaking-the-waves-review-emily-watson-adds-brilliance-to-von-triers-windup-of-a-movie" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/03/see-no-evil-why-have-baddies-vanished-from-our-cinema-screens" target="_blank">See no evil: why have baddies vanished from our cinema screens? - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Tom Cruise’s latest villain is in fact a sentient computer code. An uncomplicatedly bad villain used to feature in every action film worth its salt. But a more globalised industry has made the universally hated figure a tricky character to pull off. An action movie without a real villain? Hans Gruber would be spinning in his grave.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 15:00:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/03/see-no-evil-why-have-baddies-vanished-from-our-cinema-screens" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/03/victor-belmondo-i-wanted-to-be-an-actor-i-never-said-to-myself-yes-but-thats-what-papi-does-too" target="_blank">Victor Belmondo: ‘I wanted to be an actor – I never said to myself, yes, but that’s what Papi does too’ - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Victor Belmondo, 29, has been quietly firing up his own acting career. He is unmistakably of the same lineage as his grandfather, Jean-Paul. At his grandfather’s funeral in 2021, he described the legendary nouvelle vague star as an ‘eternal sun’ Now beginning to light up the screen himself, he talks about trying to capture his predecessor's insouciance.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 14:03:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/03/victor-belmondo-i-wanted-to-be-an-actor-i-never-said-to-myself-yes-but-thats-what-papi-does-too" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/03/rest-in-pink-can-anyone-stop-the-rise-of-the-barbie-coffin" target="_blank">Rest in pink: can anyone stop the rise of the Barbie coffin? - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The sheer number of records that Barbie has broken is nothing short of staggering. Already one of the top 100 highest-grossing films of all time. Now counts as the highest film grossing ever made by a female director. Barbie looks set to become the film that will inspire more regrettable coffin decisions than any other.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 12:40:55 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/03/rest-in-pink-can-anyone-stop-the-rise-of-the-barbie-coffin" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/02/jess-search-documentary-producer-dies-at-54" target="_blank">Documentary producer Jess Search dies at 54 - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Jess Search co-founded the non-profit Doc Society organisation. She was involved in hundreds of projects including Citizenfour, Citizenfour and Virunga. Tributes paid to the 54-year-old who 'lived a life of purpose on her own terms' She died of brain cancer at the age of 54.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 02 Aug 2023 20:52:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/02/jess-search-documentary-producer-dies-at-54" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/aug/02/george-clooney-meryl-streep-and-matt-damon-among-a-listers-donating-1m-to-help-striking-actors" target="_blank">George Clooney, Meryl Streep and Matt Damon among A-listers donating $1m to help striking actors - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> More than a dozen top tier film stars have donated more than $1m to Sag-aftra’s emergency hardship fund. $15m has so far been raised to help those hit hardest by the cessation of filming in Hollywood. The stars have followed the lead of Dwayne (The Rock) Johnson with $15million raised so far.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 02 Aug 2023 17:15:16 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/aug/02/george-clooney-meryl-streep-and-matt-damon-among-a-listers-donating-1m-to-help-striking-actors" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/01/not-big-in-japan-country-rejects-co-marketing-of-barbie-and-oppenheimer-as-trivialising-nuclear-war" target="_blank">Barbenheimer backlash: Warner Bros apologises after its Japan arm complains - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Warner Bros Japan publicly criticised US counterparts over ‘inconsiderate’ reactions to art combining playful Barbie imagery with mushroom clouds. Growing backlash in Japan against the conflation of Greta Gerwig’s playfully marketed movie with Oppenheimer, a biopic of the scientist behind the atomic bombs.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 01 Aug 2023 15:50:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/01/not-big-in-japan-country-rejects-co-marketing-of-barbie-and-oppenheimer-as-trivialising-nuclear-war" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/31/barbie-and-oppenheimers-success-continues-into-second-weekend" target="_blank">Barbie and Oppenheimer’s success continues into second weekend - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Box-office takings have rarely been healthier, with strong second weekends for both Barbie and Oppenheimer. Both films have sold-out screenings and unprecedented post-pandemic buzz. Overall, Barbie has so far made $775m globally and is already third best-performing film of the year.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 31 Jul 2023 12:48:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/31/barbie-and-oppenheimers-success-continues-into-second-weekend" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/05/mission-impossible-dead-reckoning-part-one-review-tom-cruise" target="_blank">Mission: Impossible – Dead Reckoning Part One review – Tom Cruise does it better - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Seven films in and nothing about M:I, from the star’s incredible stunt skills to the silly-serious tone, is showing any sign of slowing down. Already, the keynote stunt has become a legend: the one on the poster, the one he reportedly did – for real – six times in one day before he was satisfied. The seventh in the Mission: Impossible action franchise with Cruise starring as Ethan Hunt.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 13 Jul 2023 10:45:14 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/05/mission-impossible-dead-reckoning-part-one-review-tom-cruise" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/10/the-deepest-breath-review-stunning-netflix-documentary-freedriving" target="_blank">The Deepest Breath review – stunning Netflix documentary on freediving - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The Deepest Breath is a love story embedded in the world of free diving, the deadly extreme sport whose practitioners plunge toward the ocean floor, often wearing nothing but a wetsuit and nose plug. (Goggles are out of the question since the air pressure would cause blood vessels in the eyes to burst.)</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 10 Jul 2023 13:23:56 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/10/the-deepest-breath-review-stunning-netflix-documentary-freedriving" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/07/insidious-the-red-door-review-shoddy-horror-sequel" target="_blank">Insidious: The Red Door review – shoddy horror sequel - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Patrick Wilson makes his directorial debut with a labored legacy sequel that should hopefully close the door on the long-running franchise. The unifying premise for hit factory Blumhouse’s reliable yet reliably uninteresting moneymaker dares viewers to wonder “what if there was a creepy thing that jumped out at you, then disappeared?”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 07 Jul 2023 13:00:23 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/07/insidious-the-red-door-review-shoddy-horror-sequel" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/06/joy-ride-review-slickly-likable-asian-american-comedy-dwells-on-family-and-identity" target="_blank">Joy Ride review – slickly likable Asian-American comedy dwells on family and identity - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Laughs, high energy levels and some outrageous set pieces make this examination of the complex relationship with distant family a fun journey of self-discovery. Adele Lim, who worked on the script for Crazy Rich Asians, now makes her feature directing debut with this likable and brash Asian-American comedy.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 06 Jul 2023 06:00:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/06/joy-ride-review-slickly-likable-asian-american-comedy-dwells-on-family-and-identity" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/07/the-out-laws-review-pierce-brosnan-cant-save-limp-netflix-comedy" target="_blank">The Out-Laws review – Pierce Brosnan can’t save limp Netflix comedy - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The ex-007 plays a criminal father-in-law in an Adam Sandler-ushered action comedy that misses every time. Adam DeVine, from the cult sitcom Workaholics, is a bundle of nice-guy nerves, a cartoon beta. The true Happy Madison stinkers are the ones even he wouldn’t headline.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 07 Jul 2023 13:10:57 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/07/the-out-laws-review-pierce-brosnan-cant-save-limp-netflix-comedy" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/18/indiana-jones-and-the-dial-of-destiny-review-harrison-ford-cracks-the-whip-in-taut-sequel" target="_blank">Indiana Jones and the Dial of Destiny review - Harrison Ford cracks the whip in taut sequel - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Indiana Jones and the Dial of Destiny is the fifth Indiana Jones film in which the legendary archaeologist and whip-cracking adventurer is back for another go-around. Harrison Ford, now 80 years young, carries off with humour and style and still nailing that reluctant crooked smile.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 28 Jun 2023 16:44:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/18/indiana-jones-and-the-dial-of-destiny-review-harrison-ford-cracks-the-whip-in-taut-sequel" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/21/no-hard-feelings-review-jennifer-lawrence-comedy-plays-sex-work-for-laughs" target="_blank">No Hard Feelings review – Jennifer Lawrence comedy plays sex work for laughs - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Jennifer Lawrence plays Maddie, a woman in her early 30s who has been unlucky in love. She still lives in her childhood home, all alone since the death of her mother. She scratches a living as an Uber driver, but her car gets repossessed for non-payment of Montauk’s exorbitant property taxes on a house.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 21 Jun 2023 12:00:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/21/no-hard-feelings-review-jennifer-lawrence-comedy-plays-sex-work-for-laughs" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/19/elemental-review-fire-and-water-fall-in-love-in-multicoloured-unworldly-pixar-fable" target="_blank">Elemental review – fire and water fall in love in multicoloured, unworldly Pixar fable - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Decent family entertainment set in the city of four elements, with a message of acceptance in bricks of colour and concepts as if originated via algorithm. It is also a star-crossed love story based on that most traditional of American themes: melting-pot diversity in the big city.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 19 Jun 2023 12:00:11 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/19/elemental-review-fire-and-water-fall-in-love-in-multicoloured-unworldly-pixar-fable" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/17/fast-10-movie-review-fast-and-furious-sequel-vin-diesel" target="_blank">Fast X review – stupidly entertaining sequel offers more of the same - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The Fast & Furious franchise reached the ideal level of sublime ridiculousness with Fast Five. The films that followed have tried nobly to top the simple, lizard-brain pleasure of this moment. Fast X seems to recognize Fast Five as the top of the franchise bell curve, because it starts there, by retconning a super-villain.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 17 May 2023 16:00:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/17/fast-10-movie-review-fast-and-furious-sequel-vin-diesel" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/18/white-men-cant-jump-movie-review-jack-harlow" target="_blank">White Men Can’t Jump review – comedy remake fumbles the shot - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Sinqua Walls and Jack Harlow fail to recall the magic of the 1992 hit in a shallow and mostly unfunny nostalgia play. Vince Staples and Myles Bullock are the best couple on screen. Teyana Taylor brings her true life experience as an NBA wife to the part of Kamal’s partner, Imani.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 18 May 2023 13:37:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/18/white-men-cant-jump-movie-review-jack-harlow" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/12/the-mother-review-jennifer-lopez-netflix" target="_blank">The Mother review – Jennifer Lopez goes kick-ass in abject kidnap thriller - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> There's some real ChatGPT film-making here in this abjectly formulaic and inert Netflix thriller from director Niki Caro. Lopez plays an ex-special forces parent aiming to rescues her kid from the bad guys. One villain (Gael García Bernal) disappears from the plot about halfway in, presumably left on cutting-room floor.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 12 May 2023 01:00:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/12/the-mother-review-jennifer-lopez-netflix" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/audio/2023/aug/01/full-story-podcast-hollywood-actors-writers-strikes-sag-aftra-succession-brian-cox" target="_blank">Why is Hollywood on strike (and why Succession’s Brian Cox is joining them)? - podcast - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Production on Hollywood films and TV shows has ground to a halt because of the Sag-Aftra strike. Michael Safi speaks to Lois Beckett, a senior reporter with Guardian US, and Brian Cox, who played media boss Logan Roy in the TV series Succession, on why writers and actors can no longer make a living.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 01 Aug 2023 15:00:06 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/audio/2023/aug/01/full-story-podcast-hollywood-actors-writers-strikes-sag-aftra-succession-brian-cox" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/audio/2023/jul/28/why-do-republicans-hate-barbie-movie-podcast" target="_blank">Why do Republicans hate the Barbie movie? – podcast - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Conservatives have slated Barbie for being, among other things, too ‘woke’, anti-men and even Chinese propaganda. Is the outrage real or is it just another example of politics employing a culture war to rally the base? Jonathan Freedland and Amanda Marcotte try to figure it out.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 04:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/audio/2023/jul/28/why-do-republicans-hate-barbie-movie-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/jul/01/weekend-podcast-actor-simon-pegg-marina-hyde-on-the-benevolent-lord-lebedev-and-the-truth-about-inflammation" target="_blank">Weekend podcast: actor Simon Pegg, Marina Hyde on the benevolent Lord Lebedev, and the truth about inflammation - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Simon Pegg on joining the A-list elite and embracing home life in Blighty. Marina Hyde implores us to ignore Lord Lebedev's links to the KGB and just focus on his successes. Joel Snape reveals all you need to know about 2023’s hottest health topic: inflammation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 01 Jul 2023 04:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/jul/01/weekend-podcast-actor-simon-pegg-marina-hyde-on-the-benevolent-lord-lebedev-and-the-truth-about-inflammation" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/jun/05/our-critics-guide-to-a-summer-of-music-movies-and-culture-podcast" target="_blank">Our critics’ guide to a summer of music, movies and culture - podcast - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Guardian culture writers Alex Needham, Ellen E Jones and Michael Cragg take Nosheen Iqbal on a guided tour of the summer. They pick their picks of the best of this summer in arts and culture from the Guardian's top picks of arts and literature.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 05 Jun 2023 02:00:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/jun/05/our-critics-guide-to-a-summer-of-music-movies-and-culture-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/may/20/weekend-podcast-little-mermaid-star-halle-bailey-marina-hyde-on-the-this-morning-rift-and-the-bereaved-sex-taboo" target="_blank">Weekend podcast: Little Mermaid star Halle Bailey, Marina Hyde on the This Morning ‘rift’, and the bereaved sex taboo - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Marina Hyde talks about Holly Willoughby and Philip Schofield's alleged rift. Halle Bailey talks about overcoming self-doubt and her soulmate sister Chlöe. Author Kat Lister explores the stigma of grieving partners’ sexuality and the loss of sexual intimacy.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 20 May 2023 04:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/may/20/weekend-podcast-little-mermaid-star-halle-bailey-marina-hyde-on-the-this-morning-rift-and-the-bereaved-sex-taboo" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/21/no-more-newborns-watership-down-has-been-upgraded-to-a-pg-itll-still-terrify-children" target="_blank">Watership Down has been upgraded to a PG. That won’t stop it terrifying children | Peter Bradshaw - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The 1978 animated version of Watership Down has been upgraded from U to PG (Parental Guidance) It is a remarkable example of censoring authority becoming more puritanical over time. The overwhelming threat of violence is part of what has made Watership down so compelling.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 14:38:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/21/no-more-newborns-watership-down-has-been-upgraded-to-a-pg-itll-still-terrify-children" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/19/barbie-indie-director-film-maker-greta-gerwig" target="_blank">Has Barbie killed the indie director? Credible film-makers are shamelessly selling out | Caspar Salmon - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> One-time indie cinema darling Greta Gerwig is now making money for a megabucks toy company that sells vacuous, hypersexualised dolls – and no one bats an eyelid. Sarah Polley was asked by Disney executives to remove a peace sign badge she was wearing. When she refused, Disney blacklisted her.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 10:42:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/19/barbie-indie-director-film-maker-greta-gerwig" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/17/latest-mission-impossible-shows-the-silent-asian-stereotype-is-alive-and-well" target="_blank">Latest Mission: Impossible shows the ‘silent Asian’ stereotype is alive and well - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Pom Klementieff’s supporting role as Paris, a savage assassin, is transformed into the tired stereotype of the silent Asian. Paris is largely mute throughout the film, flying in the face of more enlightened recent film roles. The French actor, who is half Korean, barely utters a word throughout the whole thing.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 17 Jul 2023 10:10:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/17/latest-mission-impossible-shows-the-silent-asian-stereotype-is-alive-and-well" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/16/jane-birkin-a-tremendous-screen-presence-with-a-gift-for-creative-collaboration" target="_blank">Jane Birkin: a tremendous screen presence with a gift for creative collaboration | Peter Bradshaw - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Birkin made a sensational impact in Blow-Up, and went on to become a classy performer for a number of major French directors – notably Godard and Agnès Varda. She was a performer with that interesting distinction of being Anglo-French, which somehow added to her unlocatable quality: she was quite at home with both languages.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 16 Jul 2023 17:22:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/16/jane-birkin-a-tremendous-screen-presence-with-a-gift-for-creative-collaboration" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/12/best-action-movie-franchises-mission-impossible" target="_blank">I did my PhD in Hollywood action films – here’s why Mission: Impossible is the best | Clem Bastow - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The series has come to be characterised largely by Tom Cruise's spectacular stunts. But what sets them apart are Ethan Hunt’s very human qualities. The Mission: Impossible films are perhaps the key-est of my key works – for no other Hollywood franchise does action, or emotion, better.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 11 Jul 2023 23:29:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/12/best-action-movie-franchises-mission-impossible" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/27/julian-sands-an-hypnotically-exotic-actor-full-of-style-and-extravagance" target="_blank">Julian Sands: a hypnotically exotic actor full of style and extravagance - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> After the smash hit of A Room With a View, Sands’ idiosyncrasies were hard to contain in mainstream movies, but in the right roles he was mesmerising. He delivered lines at about 60 to 70% of the speed at which other actors spoke. These were mannerisms that became more pronounced and sometimes baffling as he got older.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 27 Jun 2023 21:30:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/27/julian-sands-an-hypnotically-exotic-actor-full-of-style-and-extravagance" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/22/oscars-best-stunts-john-wick" target="_blank">Academy, take action: why there should be an Oscar for best stunts - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The director of John Wick: Chapter 4 has revealed that he is in discussions with the Academy to officially recognise the power of action sequences. John Wick director John Wick is in talks with the academy to recognise action sequences in films. The Academy could be better recognised for commercial movies to be better recognised.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 22 Jun 2023 15:15:12 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/22/oscars-best-stunts-john-wick" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/15/fierce-sensual-cerebral-how-glenda-jackson-brought-class-to-cinema" target="_blank">Fierce, sensual, cerebral: how Glenda Jackson brought class to film | Peter Bradshaw - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The British actor was the epitome of countercultural chic in key 1970s films. It is just a shame she couldn't be persuaded to do more of them when her political career ended. The first Oscar was for playing Gudrun in Lawrence’s Women in Love.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 15 Jun 2023 14:03:49 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/15/fierce-sensual-cerebral-how-glenda-jackson-brought-class-to-cinema" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/07/marvel-actors-criticise-superhero-films-chris-hemsworth-elizabeth-olsen" target="_blank">Chris Hemsworth thinks Thor has become ‘too silly’ – if superheroes are turning on Marvel, is endgame nigh? - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Three Marvel stars have recently broken rank to reveal that their movies sort of suck. Hemsworth and Elizabeth Olsen are among the MCU stars to break rank and criticise their latest films. Marvel is in a slump, receiving its three lowest-ever Rotten Tomatoes scores in the last three years.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 12:47:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/07/marvel-actors-criticise-superhero-films-chris-hemsworth-elizabeth-olsen" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/05/royal-but-redundant-why-the-disney-prince-is-an-endangered-species" target="_blank">Royal but redundant: why the Disney prince is an endangered species - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> New Little Mermaid film reinforces the sense that the Disney princesses’ significant others are doomed to non-existence. The latest iteration of the character is Prince Eric in the live-action remake of The Little Mermaid. Although he has more screen time than in the original, he’s arguably even more redundant this time around.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 05 Jun 2023 08:51:49 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/05/royal-but-redundant-why-the-disney-prince-is-an-endangered-species" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/24/kenneth-anger-dark-magus-occult-desire-hollywood-babylon" target="_blank">Kenneth Anger: Tinseltown’s outrageous magus of occult desire | Peter Bradshaw - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Anger ignited the gossip industry with the squalid tales in his book Hollywood Babylon, while his daringly erotic films fuelled the counterculture. He was virtually the Aleister Crowley of movie legend. Anger's masterpiece was in the medium of the written word: his outrageous, scabrous and scurrilous supposed history of Tinseltown scandals: Hollywood Babylon.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 24 May 2023 16:55:54 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/24/kenneth-anger-dark-magus-occult-desire-hollywood-babylon" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/jul/28/star-wars-ahmed-best-interview-jar-jar-binks-the-phantom-menace-the-mandalorian" target="_blank">‘The lowest I’ve ever been’: how playing Jar Jar Binks led to abuse, near death – and saving Baby Yoda - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Ahmed Best was overjoyed when cast as Jar Jar Binks - until threats of violence began. As a podcast tells his story, he talks about hate, making movie history and a glorious comeback in The Mandalorian. TED-produced podcast tells the story of the actor who played the character in Star Wars.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 12:13:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/jul/28/star-wars-ahmed-best-interview-jar-jar-binks-the-phantom-menace-the-mandalorian" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/28/warner-bros-marketing-head-josh-goldstine-barbie-pink-movement" target="_blank">How did Barbie do it? Warner’s head of marketing on creating a ‘pink movement’ - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Greta Gerwig’s new Barbie movie broke box office records for the most commercially successful film by a female director. The film brought in more than $356m (£276m, A$527m) worldwide during its opening weekend and another $50m in tickets on Monday and Tuesday.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 10:00:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/28/warner-bros-marketing-head-josh-goldstine-barbie-pink-movement" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/28/i-was-making-a-film-about-the-trauma-of-an-entire-country-director-alice-winocour-on-her-movie-about-the-2015-paris-terror-attacks" target="_blank">‘I was making a film about the trauma of an entire country’: director Alice Winocour on her movie about the 2015 Paris terror attacks - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> After her brother was caught up in the Bataclan siege, Winocour wanted to address the events that had scarred France. Unlike the recent Jean Dujardin film November, it completely ignores religion and largely passes over the bloodshed. Instead, it joins films such as You Will Not Have My Hate and One Year, One Nigh.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 07:00:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/28/i-was-making-a-film-about-the-trauma-of-an-entire-country-director-alice-winocour-on-her-movie-about-the-2015-paris-terror-attacks" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/26/rackaracka-talk-to-me-film-danny-michael-philippou-youtube" target="_blank">‘It’s a nonstop dream’: the YouTuber twins behind Talk to Me, the scariest film of the year - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Adelaide brothers Danny and Michael Philippou, AKA RackaRacka, are in the middle of a whirlwind press tour for their horror debut, Talk to Me. The horror film unleashed a competitive bidding war at this year’s Sundance film festival and landed them a high seven-figure deal with A24.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 15:00:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/26/rackaracka-talk-to-me-film-danny-michael-philippou-youtube" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/23/tobias-menzies-interview-you-hurt-my-feelings" target="_blank">‘I’m monomaniacal, I get slightly obsessive’: actor Tobias Menzies on tennis, moon landings and people watching - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Tobias Menzies has always relished a challenge, whether it's playing Prince Philip, or a New York therapist – or just keeping up with Brad Pitt. At the beginning of the Covid pandemic, he decided to see if he could get his game back. He joined his local club in north London and started hitting, mostly on his own with a machine firing balls at him, at least a couple of times a week.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 23 Jul 2023 11:00:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/23/tobias-menzies-interview-you-hurt-my-feelings" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/jul/22/heartstoppers-kit-connor-i-wasnt-used-to-the-idea-of-millions-of-people-being-interested-in-my-private-life" target="_blank">Heartstopper’s Kit Connor: ‘I wasn’t used to the idea of millions of people being interested in my private life’ - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Kit Connor, 19, lives at home with his mum and dad - and is a megastar thanks to Netflix’s take on the teen gay love story. The actor talks about accusations of ‘queerbaiting’, being outed at 18, and Elton John.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 22 Jul 2023 06:00:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/jul/22/heartstoppers-kit-connor-i-wasnt-used-to-the-idea-of-millions-of-people-being-interested-in-my-private-life" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/21/emily-blunt-women-pressured-oppenheimer" target="_blank">Emily Blunt: ‘Women are still pressured to be warm and likable. Men are not’ - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The star of Christopher Nolan’s nuclear epic Oppenheimer discusses sexism in cinema, her support for the strikes and speaking a secret language with her sister. Emily Blunt, 17 months her senior, is a literary agent. When she reads manuscripts, she says: ‘If I’m thinking: 'Is it good?’ it's not good. If it's great, you can’t stop thinking about it'</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 04:00:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/21/emily-blunt-women-pressured-oppenheimer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/30/talk-to-me-review-danny-and-michael-philippou-an-evil-dead-for-the-snapchat-generation-danny-michael-philippou" target="_blank">Talk to Me review – an Evil Dead for the Snapchat generation - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Australian YouTuber twins Danny and Michael Philippou’s feature debut is an entertaining chiller that mixes shrieking horror and psychological nuance. Two years after the untimely death of her mother, 17-year-old Mia (Sophie Wilde) has retreated from her father, preferring to hang out at the home of her father.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 30 Jul 2023 07:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/30/talk-to-me-review-danny-and-michael-philippou-an-evil-dead-for-the-snapchat-generation-danny-michael-philippou" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/29/streaming-the-best-stop-the-wedding-films-polite-society" target="_blank">Streaming: Polite Society and the best ‘stop the wedding!’ films - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Nida Manzoor’s fizzing comedy joins the long procession of disrupted nuptials. The “stop the wedding!” film is virtually its own subgenre. The wedding targeted in the film isn’t a victim of romantic discord or envy. Instead, it's the bride's sister who simply believes it's a bad idea all round.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 29 Jul 2023 07:00:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/29/streaming-the-best-stop-the-wedding-films-polite-society" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/21/aquaman-and-the-lost-kingdom-is-in-trouble-but-is-it-too-big-to-fail" target="_blank">Aquaman and the Lost Kingdom is in trouble – but is it too big to fail? - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The Flash is on to its third reshoot and has lost two Batmans. Jason Momoa’s protector of the deep is now destined for a watery grave. The idea of making an Aquaman movie was deemed so ridiculous that Entourage spent much of its second and third seasons taking the mickey out.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 10:46:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/21/aquaman-and-the-lost-kingdom-is-in-trouble-but-is-it-too-big-to-fail" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-04/afl-live-scorecentre-stats-results-wb-rich/102636872" target="_blank">AFL live: Bulldogs make red-hot start in crucial clash against the Tigers - ABC Australia</a></h2><div class="description"> Round 21 starts with a crunch match at Docklands, as the Bulldogs defend their top eight spot against a Richmond side that wants to replace them. Follow our live AFL ScoreCentre for all the scores, stats and results at the Docklands Stadium on Friday night. Richmond will be looking to replace the Bulldogs in the top eight for the first time this year.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 09:12:59 +0000</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-04/afl-live-scorecentre-stats-results-wb-rich/102636872" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-04/zambia-women-s-world-cup-coach-under-investigation-by-fifa/102691874" target="_blank">FIFA investigates Zambia coach after misconduct complaint - ABC Australia</a></h2><div class="description"> FIFA are investigating a misconduct complaint involving Zambia's head coach Bruce Mwape. Football authorities are investigating th